gw.api.logicalmatch

Interface KeyBasedLogicalMatcher<T extends KeyableBean>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the entity type that this matcher operates against.
    All Superinterfaces:
    LogicalMatcher
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractEffDatedPropertiesMatcher, AbstractPropertiesMatcher, AbstractScheduleClauseItemMatcher

    public interface KeyBasedLogicalMatcher<T extends KeyableBean>
extends LogicalMatcher
    Defines a strongly typed LogicalMatcher interface for beans that want to match other beans of the same type.

    • Method Detail

      • isLogicalMatch

        boolean isLogicalMatch(T bean)
        Determines if the given bean is a logical match to the owner of this Delegate. The semantics of this method are similar to those in Object.equals(Object), in that if it returns true, the owning bean is logically equivalent to bean, and if it returns false, the two are not logically equivalent.
        Parameters:
        bean - the bean to compare for a match
        Returns:
        true if the given bean matches the owner of this Delegate

      • genKey

        java.lang.Object genKey()
        Description copied from interface: LogicalMatcher
        Generate a logical key for the owner of this Matching Delegate. The semantics of this key are similar to those for Object.hashCode(), i.e. if the keys are not equal, the owning beans are definitely not logically equivalent, whereas if the keys are equal, the owning beans might be logically equivalent (though LogicalMatcher.isLogicalMatchUntyped(entity.KeyableBean) must be called to confirm logical equivalence).
        Specified by:
        genKey in interface LogicalMatcher
        Returns:
        a logical key representing the owning bean of this LogicalMatcher
